    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes and pepper are almost ready, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>butter </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
